  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pistachios</strong> and toast for 2 min or until they've darkened slightly</p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>toasted pistachios</strong> to a board to cool and keep the pan</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/persian-lamb-couscous/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced red onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/persian-lamb-couscous/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>couscous</strong> and<strong> sultanas</strong> to a heatproof bowl with 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong>, cover and set aside</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/persian-lamb-couscous/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, strip the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them finely</p><p>Mix the chopped mint through the<strong> natural yoghurt</strong> – this is your<strong> minted yoghurt</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/persian-lamb-couscous/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, increase the heat to medium-high and add the<strong> lamb mince</strong></p><p>Cook for 4 min until browned, breaking the mince up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Once browned, crumble the<strong> chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>into the pan with the<strong> tomato paste</strong> and <strong>baharat</strong> and cook for 2 min</p><p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook for a further 5 min or until the lamb has crisped</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/persian-lamb-couscous/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the<strong> cucumber</strong> in half and scrape out the inner seeds with a teaspoon, discarding the watery seeds</p><p>Dice the remaining <strong>cucumber</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/persian-lamb-couscous/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Fluff the <strong>couscous</strong> with a fork, add the <strong>grated carrot</strong> and<strong> chopped cucumber</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and give everything a good mix – this is your <strong>carrot and cucumber couscous</strong></p><p>Chop the<strong> toasted pistachios </strong>roughly</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/persian-lamb-couscous/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> crispy lamb</strong> over the <strong>carrot and cucumber</strong> <strong>couscous</strong></p><p>Dollop with the <strong>minted yoghurt</strong> and garnish with the <strong>chopped pistachios</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
